Sentencas: Strontium molybdate (SrMoO3) as an electronic conductor was incorporated with yttriastabilized zirconia (YSZ) to form an anode scaffold for solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: H2 and CH4 oxidation on Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 infiltrated SrMoO3-yttria-stabilized zirconia anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (GDC) nanoparticles were introduced by wet impregnation to complete the Ni-free GDC infiltrated SrMoO3-YSZ anode fabrication.
Titulo: H2 and CH4 oxidation on Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 infiltrated SrMoO3-yttria-stabilized zirconia anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effects of SrMoO3 on the electrode conductivity and GDC infiltration on the catalytic activity were examined.
Titulo: H2 and CH4 oxidation on Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 infiltrated SrMoO3-yttria-stabilized zirconia anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A pronounced performance improvement was observed both on wet H-2 and CH4 oxidation for the 56 wt.% GDC infiltrated SrMoO3-YSZ.
Titulo: H2 and CH4 oxidation on Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 infiltrated SrMoO3-yttria-stabilized zirconia anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In particular, the polarization resistance decreased from 8 cm(2) to 0.5 Omega cm(2) under wet H-2 (3% H2O) at 800 degrees C with the introduction of GDC.
Titulo: H2 and CH4 oxidation on Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 infiltrated SrMoO3-yttria-stabilized zirconia anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Under wet CH4 at 900 degrees C, a maximum power density of 160 mW cm(2) was obtained and no carbon deposition was observed on the anode.
Titulo: H2 and CH4 oxidation on Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 infiltrated SrMoO3-yttria-stabilized zirconia anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It was found that the addition of H2O in the anode caused an increase of electrode ohmic resistance and a decrease of open circuit voltage.
Titulo: H2 and CH4 oxidation on Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 infiltrated SrMoO3-yttria-stabilized zirconia anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Redox cycling stability was investigated and only a slight drop in cell performance was observed after 5 cycles.
Titulo: H2 and CH4 oxidation on Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 infiltrated SrMoO3-yttria-stabilized zirconia anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These results suggest that GDC infiltrated SrMoO3-YSZ is a promising anode material for solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: H2 and CH4 oxidation on Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 infiltrated SrMoO3-yttria-stabilized zirconia anode for solid oxide fuel cells
